		Senior Leadership Team	








Senior Leadership Team 











Judith S. Love

Judith S. Love is president of Comerica's California Market.  She also serves as a member of Comerica's Management Executive Committee.
She assumed her current position on Dec. 1, 2013, succeeding J. Michael Fulton, who retired in April 2014.  Love has been responsible for Middle Market Banking - Northern California, as well as International Finance. She was named Executive Vice President in 2009.
Love joined Comerica in 1982.  During her more than 30-year career with the bank, she has held positions with increasing responsibility, including president of Comerica Securities, Inc., as well as roles in investor relations, finance, treasury, real estate and purchasing.
Love received her bachelor's degree from Central Michigan University and a Masters of Business Administration from the University of Detroit. 
Among her professional and community affiliations, Love served as a board member of The Professional BusinessWomen of California and a member of Association for Corporate Growth.  She is a Graduate from the Center for Creative Leadership Program, was recognized as one of the Bay Area’s Most Influential Women in Business, and serves on the California Bankers Association Board of Directors.
December 2016


