Nica


Age: 25-34
Gender: female

 






3 Stars Out Of 5



Not What I Was Hoping For


March  5, 2015



Nica




Age: 25-34
Gender: female
  
            I really wanted to like this book but sadly it was not my favorite. However, the historical content was interesting as was learning about the brickmaking business. The main character, Laura, and her mother sell their brickmaking business to Ewan and his uncle who have a tenuous relationship. They don't agree on how to run the business which creates conflict. Ewan wants to run the company in the best and wisest way possible so Laura agrees to help as she grew up in the business and is very knowledgeable. There are other characters in the book but they cause a lot of conflict and drama I found that annoyed me which is one of the reasons I did not like this book. 


I give this book 3 out of 5 stars as it was well written but not an enjoyable read as I would have liked.


I received a free copy of this book from Bethany House in exchange for an honest review.

        














