Reviews & Community QA





Judith Ripka Sterling Diamonique Heart 8" Bracelet is rated
    3.2 out of
    5 by
    5.







            Rated 5 out of
            5
 by
        Sita21 from
        Understated elegance
This Judith Ripka bracelet is truly an everyday piece. The bracelet feels substantial on your wrist. I love that there is a hidden clasp on it. It's one of the most understated but elegant bracelets I own. I too ordered the 8" bracelet after reading that the bracelet ran small. It fits perfectly. The hearts are beautiful but they also remind me of paw prints so you can think of it that way as well.
Date published: 2017-07-01





            Rated 5 out of
            5
 by
        Sammycat1 from
        Elegance made just right
I've been a collector of Judith's jewelry for decades, and sometimes I'm not in the mood for her larger pieces -- but I still love her design aesthetic. I was attracted to this piece because it contains many of her design trademarks: the panther with berge carving, her diamonique-kissed hearts and the solid clasp.

For a smaller, more everyday look, this bracelet still has a decent amount of heft and subtle sparkle ... an elegant look on a more diminutive scale. A winner!
Date published: 2016-10-06





            Rated 4 out of
            5
 by
        candyagain from
        Well -- I love this bracelet
I am very pleased with this bracelet. It is more appropriate for every day wear than some of my more ornate JR bracelets. It is flat so it doesn't catch on things. The clasp is sturdy and I think it has a nice weight to it. I'm very pleased with this item. I wear more of a 7 1/2 inch bracelet and find the 7 and 3/4 length better for the workday. The DQ hearts are a nice touch and the lower setting is again better for practical wearing.
Date published: 2016-10-05





            Rated 1 out of
            5
 by
        Carole W from
        Nothing Special
I love Judith Ripka and have a ton of her items which I love. However, I was unimpressed with this bracelet. I purchased as a wear-everyday-with-everythng bracelet similar to a tennis bracelet but was disappointed that it barely shows up on the wrist. It is small and very lightweight and the hearts have no bling and just "aren't there!" In fact, I could not feel it on my wrist and was so afraid i'd lose it without knowing. I would like this style better without the hearts with the same design links only broader and heavier. The fastener was difficult for me as well. I ordered the 8" which fit more like a 7 1/4." which made it difficult to open and close. I believe this bracelet is more for someone with a very small wrist. Though my wrist is average 7 1/4" it is not for me. Sorry, Judith, I love most of your items. This one just isn't for me.
Date published: 2016-09-25





            Rated 1 out of
            5
 by
        LLF from
        WORST PURCHASE FROM JR
The host was raving on and on about how this was the best bracelet Judith has ever done. I am shocked because this was my absolute worst purchase from Judith Ripka's line. The bracelet is so light weight it is unbelievable! The links kink and are difficult to straighten. It looks like a bracelet that I would purchase for my 10 year old niece. I own a LOT of Judith's pieces and love her line, but lately everything I've received from her is horrible and I've had to pay to return it. Bring us the quality pieces that we were all use to, not all this cheap dime store quality jewelry.
Date published: 2016-09-22






