Reviews & Community QA





Judith Ripka Verona 8" Heart & Key Charm Bracelet 36.9g Sterling is rated
    3.0 out of
    5 by
    7.







            Rated 1 out of
            5
 by
        Mehndi from
        I keep trying....
To like Judith....this bracelet seemed a lot nicer on line and tv....bought at a reduced price and can't imagine it at the regular price. ..not even worth the sale price. It looks cheap. I bought the colored version and didn't realize it's almost striped looking, and the heart is thin and key tiny.
Date published: 2016-06-10





            Rated 5 out of
            5
 by
        chrisq2 from
        Love, love, love these
I love this bracelet so much more than I expected to. I thought it would be like the smaller verona bracelet and therefore waaay overpriced. Instead, I found this bracelet has large chunky links with great texture. These links have deeper grooves, which I love, and for me the colors are fantastic. I bought the rose, the sterling and then the yellow. I got them all "as is" and am thrilled with each one.
I love the look of the frosty silver color. The yellow is a little tight on me because I had to get the 7 1/4" because there was no 8" in yellow "as is." The yellow one is particularly gorgeous because of its rich buttery color.
I think I missed out on the black, but hopefully it'll show up "as is" in the 8" or the 7 1/4." My wrist measures 7 1/4", so I can use either size. I prefer the larger size, but either will do, if you have the same size wrist as me.
I'd love to have a necklace in this link, but I'm sure it would cost a fortune. Thanks for "as is" QVC, no way could I have these without it. I really appreciate the low prices and sometimes even EP on "as is" items.
Date published: 2015-09-26





            Rated 5 out of
            5
 by
        Starshine9 from
        Love My Heart Bracelet
I love my Chocolate Heart Bracelet! Yes, it is difficult to clasp, and yes, it could use a few more links for a drapier fit, but it is gorgeous! The Diamonique heart and key are so sparkly and sweet. I love the chocolate brown color and the shimmer of the links. I wear my bracelet often! Love those Judith Ripka hearts!
Date published: 2015-08-31





            Rated 4 out of
            5
 by
        vll from
        Beautiful But Not Long Enough
Loved it but because it is so chunky, needs to be longer in length to work for my wrist. Always a problem with me. Perhaps Judith you could devise a textured link to extend like they do on the watches. I tried my trustee magnets but due to the thickness of the links, which are beautiful, it doesn't work. I'll keep trying as when it does work it's a keeper.
Date published: 2015-08-29





            Rated 2 out of
            5
 by
        fata from
        Beautiful But........
I love the design of this bracelet. The heart and key and the overall design. I ordered the sterling silver version and ultimately decided to keep the bracelet but I am taking it to a jeweler to have extra links added. I ordered the 8 inch version and it is extremely difficult to clasp without assistance from another person. This is why the low review. It is not an inexpensive bracelet so I would think it should actually be longer than 8 inches so that it would fit like an 8 inch bracelet.
Date published: 2015-03-09





            Rated 3 out of
            5
 by
        Half Angel from
        Nice bracelet too hard to put on
I have to return this item. I ordered the cheapie $89 JR bracelet and had to return that, no clasp end, you were just supposed to clasp to a link! Now this bracelet actually has a clasp end it's just too darn small and the bracelet too tight to clasp properly. I have a 7" wrist and this 8" bracelet just did not have enough chain for me to clasp it. Unless you want a bracelet that is hard to put on-- don't bother. Tired of returning JR items.
Date published: 2015-03-01





            Rated 1 out of
            5
 by
        nanajoyce from
        Beautiful but not well made
I was absolutely thrilled to receive the bracelet. It was gorgeous, and it immediately attracted a number of compliments. However, after wearing it daily for 1 week, the charms suddenly just disconnected and fell to the ground while I was simply walking in my apartment....definitely not up to Judith Ripka's usual standards. So, I am returning the bracelet (sadly).
Date published: 2015-02-19






